track_notes:
We camped at Oak Flat Camground and walked from there, this adds about 3 miles to the loop. The first bit of the walk is through a creek, the area is stunning with really amazing rock formations (hoodoos), but it is slow going. If you drive/walk to the mine gate, there should be a dirt road to the west which will take you to the climbers trail which we joined about 2h in. The climbers trail is well marked with many cairns, and takes you to Apache Leap.

From Apache leap you are off-trail bushwhacking and wayfinding. It is not a hard hike, it is just a long day. There was water in the North Tank. Views are incredible all day. The summit of Apache Benchmark is plenty big enough for a wire antenna, has a summit log and a couple of benchmarks. Picketpost looks tiny from up there. I hit north and south PHX with 23cm.

NOTE: History of the area is brutal, with a lot of massacres of indigenous people. Currently the mine is threatening to destroy the landscape and make the area inaccessible.
track_title: Via Apache Leap, mostly off trail.
